Olive Oil
1 packet freekeh
3.5 cup water
1 sachet vegetable stock powder
2 parsnip
1 onion
1 packet peeled pumpkin pieces
1 sachet chermoula spice blend
1 bag salad leaves
½ lemon
1 packet roasted almonds
1 packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise
½ tbs honey
1 bunch mint
1 block Greek salad cheese/feta cheese

Preheat the oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced. Rinse the freekeh. In a large saucepan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over a medium-high heat. Add the freekeh and toast until fragrant, 2 minutes. Add the water and vegetable stock powder. Bring to the boil, then reduce to a medium-high heat and cook until tender, 30-35 minutes. Drain the freekeh and return to the saucepan. Cover to keep warm and set aside.

While the freekeh is cooking, peel and cut the parsnip into 2cm chunks. Slice the red onion
into 2cm wedges. Divide the peeled & chopped pumpkin, parsnip, onion and chermoula spice blend over two oven trays lined with baking paper. Drizzle with olive oil, season with salt and pepper and toss to coat. Cook until tender, 20-25 minutes.
TIP: Cut the veggies to size so they cook in time. TIP: If your oven tray is crowded, divide between two trays.

While the veggies are roasting, roughly chop the spinach & rocket mix. Zest the lemon to get a pinch, then slice into wedges. Roughly chop the roasted almonds. In a small bowl, combine the dill & parsley mayonnaise with a dash of water. Set aside.

In a second small bowl, combine the honey, lemon zest, a generous squeeze of lemon juice and a generous drizzle of olive oil. Season with salt and pepper. Mix well.

Add the roasted veggies, spinach & rocket and honey dressing to the freekeh, then toss
to combine.

Pick and thinly slice the mint leaves. Divide the roast pumpkin, parsnip and freekeh salad between bowls. Top with the dill-parsley dressing and crumble over the cheese. Garnish with the almonds and mint. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges.